				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \frac{Z}{{\displaystyle {\sum}_i^n}{Z}_i} $$\end{document}Z∑inZi. The idea is that under neutrality the more mutable a region is the more likely it is to carry mutations. By using this resampling method, we preserve the number of regions containing pathogenic variants and therefore the number of zeros and ones in our response vector remains the same.

